1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with social networks and their de-anonymization, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a novel graph slicing technique, which could be considered a software engineering approach to solving the de-anonymization problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses mathematical analysis to study the de-anonymization problem, which could be considered a systems and control approach. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses bootstrap percolation, which is a graph-based algorithm, to solve the de-anonymization problem. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses simulation experiments to validate the results, which could be considered a computational science approach.
